      • getRelationMap

        public java.util.Map<T,java.util.Set<T>> getRelationMap()
        Description copied from interface: IUpperSemiLattice
        If y ∈ Y and x is mapped to Y, then xRy (with R as the partially ordered strict relation of the semilattice). The mapping here is non-reflexive : if xRy, then x ≠ y.
        Specified by:
        getRelationMap in interface IUpperSemiLattice<T>
        Returns:
        the semilattice as a mapping from any element to its strict lower bounds
